# Quality standards

## Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)

- Interactive elements must have accessible labels (`aria-label`, `aria-labelledby`, or visible text)
- Images must have meaningful `alt` text (empty `alt=""` for decorative images)
- Keyboard navigation must work: focus rings must be visible
- Color contrast ratio ≥ 4.5:1 for text
- Use semantic HTML (`<button>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<article>`)

```tsx
// ❌
<div onClick={handleClick}>Click me</div>

// ✅
<button onClick={handleClick}>Click me</button>
```

## SEO

- Every page exports `metadata` or `generateMetadata`
- `<title>` and `<meta name="description">` always set
- Use Next.js `<Image>` component — never raw `<img>` for content images
- Heading hierarchy: one `<h1>` per page, then `<h2>` → `<h3>`

## Performance

- `"use client"` only when strictly needed (event handlers, hooks, browser APIs)
- Default to Server Components
- Dynamic imports for heavy components: `next/dynamic`
- No inline functions in JSX render for expensive computations → `useMemo` / `useCallback`

## Code hygiene

- No `console.log` in committed code
- No commented-out code blocks
- No `TODO` without a linked GitHub issue number
- Remove unused imports and variables before committing
